sylk-pushserver (2.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added mobile tokens storage
  * Added v2 routes for storage API
  * Fixed debian packaging
  * Cleaned up log functions
  * Changed shebang so it runs in a virtual env
  * Refactored configuration loading
  * Use payload fix function
  * Return more usefull errors if request validation fails
  * Added pushclient to use v2 API
  * Added support for Message push notifications
  * Support 'fcm' as platform name
  * Support 'apns' as platform name

 -- Adrian Georgescu <ag@ag-projects.com>  Sat, 12 Dec 2020 12:32:53 +0100

